node.title: Sheffield Shield match postponed due to possible COVID case
node.alt: A wide shot of cricketers on the SCG
node.description: The match between NSW and Victoria will not begin this morning as scheduled following bowler Will Sutherland returningÂ a test "which requires further analysis".
node.content:
["The Sheffield Shield match between New South Wales and Victoria will not start this morning as scheduled due to a possible COVID-19 case.", "Cricket Australia said Victorian bowler Will Sutherland \"returned a test result which requires further analysis\" in the course of routine testing.", "The Victorian team is self-isolating while further investigations take place.", "The decision to defer the match came just hours before Friday's toss, which was scheduled for\u00a010:00am AEDT.", "Officials are looking into the situation and contemplating what the possible flow-on effects will be.", "If the match was to be postponed it would be the second first-class fixture to be moved on the morning of day one this season.", "A Shield match between Tasmania and Queensland suffered a similar fate last month due to border concerns amid fears of an outbreak in Brisbane.", "Victoria have won the previous two Shield encounters between the sides comfortably, with Australia's Test players not taking part in this match.", "", "
COVID cases surging across several European countries
", "ABC/AAP"]
